Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.87,0:00:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers, do you know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.88,0:00:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see this finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.34,0:00:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.30,0:00:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you answer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.06,0:00:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.94,0:00:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.61,0:00:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...nster... coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.36,0:00:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming?  What's coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster... is coming....
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.29,0:00:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.24,0:02:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(358,334)\fad(200,155)}Night of the Execution
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.63,0:02:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you can speak now, Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The four middle aged couples murdered \N in the past two years...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.56,0:02:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were seen near three of those crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.89,0:02:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Adolf Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.11,0:02:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.03,0:02:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're employed as a lock picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:03:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your job is to merely open locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.62,0:03:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't possibly have slit their throats \N in such a splendidly horizontal fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.84,0:03:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there were others besides you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.88,0:03:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way I see it, there had to have \N been at least three people...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in order to get past the strong locks and kill the middle aged couples without resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.90,0:03:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're pretty much done narrowing the list \N of suspects who are skilled with knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of time before we determine \N who your partners were...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...whether you tell us or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.87,0:03:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't what I really want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to know why you bothered to go all \N over Germany to commit those four crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.59,0:03:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why you only killed childless middle aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.47,0:03:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valuables were taken, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.68,0:03:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...after splitting such a small amount \N between the three of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.35,0:04:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this crime doesn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.81,0:04:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we make a plea bargain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.65,0:04:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you confess now, we'll dismiss all charges against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who hired you guys for these jobs?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.67,0:04:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.71,0:04:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay!  It's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.42,0:04:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This interrogation has gone far enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.01,0:04:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we just need to push a little further.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.72,0:04:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an order from the attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.35,0:04:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's fine.  I'll return some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.44,0:04:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be leaving some observers behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to make sure he isn't poisoned \N or doesn't disappear on us...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:05:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that trouble seems to follow \N you for some reason, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.20,0:05:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.87,0:05:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.33,0:05:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.55,0:05:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just out for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.47,0:05:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just do these kinds of things by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.23,0:05:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The patient needs a change of scenery once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.85,0:05:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're only going out to the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.65,0:05:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're so worried, why don't you just come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so nice and warm today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can talk now, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.67,0:05:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's days like today that make me really glad to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.93,0:06:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At times, I feel like I wouldn't be able \N to go on without these kinds of days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially when faced with life \N and death each and every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.31,0:06:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's easier for doctors if they \N only focus on promotions or research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be like that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.57,0:06:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to get promoted so I could do my own research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.41,0:06:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that being successful in surgery \N was the only way to secure my position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.62,0:06:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I changed as a result of operating \N on a certain little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.42,0:06:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a twin... the older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By saving his life after he was shot in the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.05,0:06:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I was able to get back to being a real doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.01,0:06:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made me realize that all human lives are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.93,0:06:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that it's a doctor's job to save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People can change for the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.61,0:07:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's never too late to start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.83,0:07:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.50,0:07:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I aren't that far apart in age, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.89,0:07:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You feel like a parent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.85,0:07:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, looks like I just gained quite a large son!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a child, I always wanted a mechanical clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.90,0:07:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.40,0:07:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the kind where the wooden Nutcracker soldier \N comes out every time it strikes an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.66,0:07:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dreamed of that clock every day, and always \N had my face up against the shop window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.75,0:07:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That shop was the first one I ever broke into.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.92,0:08:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was caught immediately that time, \N and couldn't get the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after that, picking locks became my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I just wanted that clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.39,0:08:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted that clock, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.54,0:08:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Confess everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.07,0:08:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the police everything, and start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.50,0:08:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All my partners...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.19,0:08:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.38,0:08:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.63,0:08:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By that monster you were talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.19,0:08:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better make it tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.40,0:09:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went through a lot of trouble to set this up just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.73,0:09:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the daughter of a state legislator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.82,0:09:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess she's what people call a \N woman with wit and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.95,0:09:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's fine, I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.45,0:09:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't know until I meet her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.08,0:09:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should start settling down...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unthinkable for a man in your \N position to not have a wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.67,0:09:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.84,0:09:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kind where a wooden Nutcracker soldier \N comes out every time it strikes an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.27,0:09:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.65,0:09:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the clock in the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.65,0:09:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.34,0:09:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for your date!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.41,0:09:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People can change for the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's never too late to start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.81,0:10:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.31,0:10:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.14,0:10:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.56,0:10:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.07,0:10:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But can you call Dr. Tenma over?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.91,0:10:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.17,0:10:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's late, but can I enter the ward?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.01,0:10:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure.  Go right ahead, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.18,0:10:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.06,0:10:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found something nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.24,0:11:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.95,0:11:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.66,0:11:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.92,0:11:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Candy...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.30,0:11:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.71,0:11:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.20,0:11:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poisoned by candy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:11:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My patient disappearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.74,0:12:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just like what happened nine years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.79,0:12:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.40,0:12:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.53,0:12:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.28,0:12:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.16,0:12:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back to the hospital, Mr. Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.62,0:12:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything will be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.38,0:12:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.17,0:12:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:12:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not look at him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.68,0:13:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who killed off my partners!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll kill you too, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.82,0:13:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.45,0:13:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.07,0:13:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come any closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.41,0:13:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved my life nine years ago, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.67,0:13:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nine years ago...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably already forgot about those two little twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.63,0:14:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, those twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.17,0:14:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you do remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.92,0:14:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.92,0:14:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll kill you too, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.43,0:14:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you going to do to him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.39,0:14:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers is my patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.14,0:14:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.15,0:14:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Execute him, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.36,0:14:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.07,0:14:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who killed off my partners!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.45,0:14:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were hired by him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.87,0:14:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We always received phone calls from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time we finished a job...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.62,0:14:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he transferred a large sum of money to a bank account...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.79,0:14:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and we'd split it between the three of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.26,0:14:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the client who ordered the murders \N of the four middle aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.47,0:14:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.10,0:14:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the police were onto us, \N we became obstacles to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.10,0:14:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fritz, the knife user, the Big Boris...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.94,0:15:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's killed them already!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.52,0:15:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before he died, Fritz told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.57,0:15:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that we'd been hired by a monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.24,0:15:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't even blink at killing someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.74,0:15:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!  He's going to kill you too, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.25,0:15:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You like to talk, don't you, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.17,0:15:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.59,0:15:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.09,0:15:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Junkers doesn't seem to know your identity, but I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.72,0:15:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was your attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.80,0:15:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Johan Liebert, the elder of the twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.47,0:15:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The East German trade adviser who fled in 1986...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.40,0:15:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're the son of Michael Liebert!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.48,0:15:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible for you to run if I know about your past!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.82,0:15:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't commit any more sins, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.62,0:15:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.62,0:15:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there were times when I was called by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.63,0:16:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.88,0:16:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody must know my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those four couples, and the Liebert family...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's different with you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're like a parent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.31,0:16:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parent?  Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.77,0:16:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if you didn't exist, I wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't kill people!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.49,0:16:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.00,0:16:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you take human lives for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.67,0:16:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was only able to get back to being \N a real doctor by saving your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that human lives have equal value by saving you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.30,0:16:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody has the right to take another's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.30,0:17:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been living as a doctor with that \N engraved upon my heart for years!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.52,0:17:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.95,0:17:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you became the chief of the surgical department \N after that incident, right Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.08,0:17:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really glad you were promoted \N to the position of head surgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in that position today because the director, \N head surgeon, and chief are dead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.68,0:17:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.93,0:17:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... it was you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.27,0:17:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it yourself, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it when I regained consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.78,0:17:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hated them so much that you wanted to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.33,0:18:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.83,0:18:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.08,0:18:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are better off dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only did what you wished for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.18,0:18:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.56,0:18:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.27,0:18:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:19:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have died back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you brought me back to life, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.45,0:19:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a down pour...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.12,0:19:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I hate rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.21,0:19:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It washes away all the evidence of a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.35,0:20:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, here is where we stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.31,0:20:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's piece together what you told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In 1986, Mr. Liebert fled from East Germany with the twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After their exile, the members of the Liebert family were shot, and both parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.37,0:20:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The older brother suffered a severe head injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.37,0:20:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You operated on that boy and saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.13,0:20:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, to your surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.34,0:20:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the boy killed the director, head surgeon, and department chief with poisoned candy, and ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.39,0:20:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And last night, he reappeared after nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.47,0:20:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He killed a county police officer \N with poisoned candy yet again...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and shot Adolf Junkers to death right in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.19,0:21:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who hired Junkers and two other \N men to kill the four middle aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Johan Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.58,0:21:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it goes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.73,0:21:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let him go for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unthinkable that someone in his position \N would commit such awful crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.31,0:21:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has an alibi for the time when the officer was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.57,0:21:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, no traces of gunpowder were found on his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we've lost the only lead we had on solving \N four murder cases of the middle aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.53,0:21:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we check out this Johan Liebert \N person, Inspector Lunge?
